Serializable
public class InvalidMessageException
extends NimException

A type of NimException that indicates that an invalid message was encountered. This is thrown if the SDK is trying to read a message "off the wire" and encounters a corrupt sequence of bytes (for example, if the length indicated in the header does not match the length of the data segment).
